 05:26 PM PARIS - Long the envy of other cities, Paris' underground metro system, which is now creaking, has become a subject of daily frustration for users, just as the French capital gears up to host this year's Olympics.\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1569784213481124e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7597217092228857, \"rank\": 0.31180567804224973, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 374}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP PublishedApr\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"UpdatedApr\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"05:26\", \"from\": 433, \"to\": 438}, {\"ngram\": \"PARIS - Long the envy\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"other cities\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"a subject\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"daily frustration\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 578}, {\"ngram\": \"users\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's Olympics\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's really difficult and we are not even at the Olympics yet when there'll be millions of people on it,\\\" Ms Juliette Fayaud, a 26-year-old restaurant worker, told AFP on the platform of the Line 8.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"score\": 0.9999999747396945, \"rank\": 2.526052531635906e-08, \"text\": \"Juliette\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\"}, {\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999996466163508, \"rank\": 3.533591118084051e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 748}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"a 26-year-old restaurant worker\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"the platform\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 844}, {\"ngram\": \"the Line\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are not enough trains.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough trains\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes in rush hour, there is a train every five minutes when you need them every two or three,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rush hour\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"a train\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"User satisfaction has plunged since the Covid-19 pandemic in 2020 when the RATP, which runs the capital's transport system, cut services as workers stayed home en masse.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1171, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"User satisfaction\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-19\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"the RATP\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's transport system\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"services\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many metro employees were furloughed and never returned to jobs, while the training of new staff to replace them slowed significantly.\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Many metro employees\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"jobs\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"the training\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"new staff\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it'll be horrible during the Olympics,\\\" 22-year-old saleswoman Gabrielle Camus, another daily user, told AFP, as she waited for a train.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Drake\", \"score\": 0.9999941475583272, \"rank\": 5.852476111052466e-06, \"text\": \"Gabrielle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Drake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Drake\"}, {\"begin\": 1391, \"end\": 1396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Camus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.262323541180969e-22, \"text\": \"Camus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Camus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Camus\"}, {\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 0.9999996466163508, \"rank\": 3.533591118084051e-07, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"another daily user\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1416}, {\"ngram\": \"a train\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am planning to use a bike and avoid the metro as much as possible.\\\"\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bike\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"the metro\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1503}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around one in five trains ran late on some metro lines in Paris last year, according to public data, with users sometimes facing waits of up to 10 or 15 minutes during the day on the worst-performing lines.\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1569784213481124e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five trains\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"some metro lines\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"public data\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"users\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"waits\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 10 or 15 minutes\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"the worst-performing lines\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Commuters on the larger overground trains, which run on so-called RER lines, were offered refunds in 2023 for the third consecutive year due to punctuality problems.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\", \"score\": 0.9917745834546056, \"rank\": 0.008281197463708144, \"text\": \"RER\", \"types\": [\"Q728937\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Commuters\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1744}, {\"ngram\": \"the larger overground trains\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1776}, {\"ngram\": \"refunds\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"the third consecutive year\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"punctuality problems\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The service is still not back to pre-Covid levels.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1951, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The service\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1912}, {\"ngram\": \"pre-Covid levels\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With around seven million visitors expected in Paris during the Olympics from July 26 to August 11, the commuter train system will be under severe scrutiny as one of the main forms of transport for tourists and locals alike.\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1569784213481124e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around seven million visitors\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2035}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"the commuter train system\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"severe scrutiny\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2108}, {\"ngram\": \"the main forms\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"transport\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Major political pressure ahead of the Games - and the appointment of former prime minister Jean Castex as head of the RATP in 2022 - has led to gradual improvements in recent months, according to surveys by the capital's transport authority.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Castex\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jean Castex\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Castex\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Castex\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Major political pressure\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"the appointment\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2289}, {\"ngram\": \"the RATP\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2301}, {\"ngram\": \"gradual improvements\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"recent months\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"surveys\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's transport authority\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2419}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Castex warned in December that eight out of 10 lines were \\\"no longer in a state to provide a quality public service\\\" which he blamed on \\\"40 years of under-investment\\\".\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2425, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castex_government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.758340735695083e-26, \"text\": \"Castex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castex_government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castex_government\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"December\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2450}, {\"ngram\": \"eight out of 10 lines\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"a state\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"a quality public service\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"40 years\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2570}, {\"ngram\": \"under-investment\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But thanks in part to a major staff recruitment drive, all lines - with the exception of the 3, the 8 and the RER C - reached the minimum performance standard of 90 per cent punctuality in March, according to the latest data.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2612}, {\"ngram\": \"a major staff recruitment drive\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"all lines\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2658}, {\"ngram\": \"the exception\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"the RER C\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"the minimum performance standard\", \"from\": 2720, \"to\": 2752}, {\"ngram\": \"90 per cent punctuality\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2788}, {\"ngram\": \"the latest data\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Workers are also racing to complete key line extensions ahead of the Olympics, notably to connect the southern Orly airport to the line 14 and a new transport node near the Stade de France, which will host athletics, in the north.\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Workers\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2828}, {\"ngram\": \"key line extensions\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2876}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2898}, {\"ngram\": \"the southern Orly airport\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 2944}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2956}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3036}, {\"ngram\": \"the north\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3050}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a challenge that we are able to meet,\\\" the head of the greater Paris region, Ms Valerie Pecresse, told reporters, as she presented her transport plans for the Olympics in late March.\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 0.9991471014747252, \"rank\": 0.0008536265823548164, \"text\": \"greater Paris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 3139, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Little_Red_Riding_Hood\", \"score\": 0.994675514314805, \"rank\": 0.00535298712821525, \"text\": \"Valerie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Little_Red_Riding_Hood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Little_Red_Riding_Hood\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3070}, {\"ngram\": \"the head\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"reporters\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3171}, {\"ngram\": \"her transport plans\", \"from\": 3190, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3226}, {\"ngram\": \"late March\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some metro or RER lines, particularly those serving the football, tennis or athletics stadiums, will have up to 71 per cent more trains than a usual summer's day.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3257, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\", \"score\": 0.9917745834546056, \"rank\": 0.008281197463708144, \"text\": \"RER\", \"types\": [\"Q728937\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_A\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some metro\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3253}, {\"ngram\": \"particularly those\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"the football, tennis or athletics stadiums\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3337}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 71 per cent more trains\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3378}, {\"ngram\": \"a usual summer's day\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenge is not so much the volume of travellers - overall traffic is expected to be no higher than a normal working day - but it is the peaks in demand as fans enter and leave stadiums.\", \"from\": 3407, \"to\": 3598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The challenge\", \"from\": 3407, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"the volume\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3446}, {\"ngram\": \"travellers\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3460}, {\"ngram\": \"- overall traffic\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3478}, {\"ngram\": \"a normal working day\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3532}, {\"ngram\": \"the peaks\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"demand\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3564}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3572}, {\"ngram\": \"stadiums\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You should not be scared to do a bit of walking,\\\" Ms Pecresse told Parisians.\", \"from\": 3600, \"to\": 3678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3637}, {\"ngram\": \"walking\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3648}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms Pecresse\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3662}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's good for your health.\\\"\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your health\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a city that has been gradually squeezing out cars, Paris is also keen to show off its recent cycling revolution.\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3763, \"end\": 3768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1569784213481124e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3718}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3761}, {\"ngram\": \"its recent cycling revolution\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each Olympic sports venue will be accessible on bike, with around 415km of new cycle lanes built ahead of the Games, as well as 20,000 cycle parking spots.\", \"from\": 3826, \"to\": 3981, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each Olympic sports venue\", \"from\": 3826, \"to\": 3851}, {\"ngram\": \"bike\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3878}, {\"ngram\": \"around 415km\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3897}, {\"ngram\": \"new cycle lanes\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3941}, {\"ngram\": \"20,000 cycle parking spots\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be no parking provision for cars at sports venues, however, and traffic jams in the capital are expected to be worse than usual due to road closures.\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no parking provision\", \"from\": 3997, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4026}, {\"ngram\": \"sports venues\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4043}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic jams\", \"from\": 4058, \"to\": 4070}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 4074, \"to\": 4085}, {\"ngram\": \"road closures\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chief organiser Tony Estanguet sounded confident last week that the city's trains, buses, trams and cycle lanes could handle the strain.\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4281, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4161, \"end\": 4175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city's trains\", \"from\": 4209, \"to\": 4226}, {\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4233}, {\"ngram\": \"trams\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4240}, {\"ngram\": \"cycle lanes\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4256}, {\"ngram\": \"the strain\", \"from\": 4270, \"to\": 4280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a key issue for the smooth organisation and 